loads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-10-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-10-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-10-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-10-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-10-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-10-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-10-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-10-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-10-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-10-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-10.jpg 1490w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px\"/\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\nNext, racers tested their mettle on the Canyon Carve, Dune Climb, and Canyon Relay courses, kicking up thick white sand left, right, and center. Typically, most of the bikes there looked like they shouldn’t have been anywhere near a dirt track—either because they were out of their element, or because they were too gorgeous to scratch.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7-745x497.jpg\" alt=\"The 2024 Malle Canyon festival outside Lisbon, Portugal\" width=\"745\" height=\"497\" srcset=\"https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-7.jpg 1490w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px\"/\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\nAlong with a strong local contingent, competitors came from the United Kingdom, Spain, Switzerland, France, Belgium, and Germany, and as far abroad as the USA, Australia, and South Africa. The legendary Troy Lee was present too, as was the ever-stylish Dimitri Coste.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOn the final day, racers battled it out in the event’s grand finale: the Canyon Derby. A combination of the Canyon Carve and Dune Climb, riders went head to head in straight knock-out rounds to crown the King or Queen of the Canyon. British rider Kirk Catherick took the gold, narrowly beating Lisbon local Tomás Blades.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15-745x497.jpg\" alt=\"The 2024 Malle Canyon festival outside Lisbon, Portugal\" width=\"745\" height=\"497\" srcset=\"https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15-745x497.jpg 745w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15-420x280.jpg 420w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15-180x120.jpg 180w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15-768x512.jpg 768w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15-570x380.jpg 570w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15-135x90.jpg 135w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15-1200x801.jpg 1200w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15-258x172.jpg 258w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15-360x240.jpg 360w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15-720x480.jpg 720w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15-275x183.jpg 275w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15-150x100.jpg 150w, https://kickstart.bikeexif.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/2024-malle-canyon-report-15.jpg 1490w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 745px) 100vw, 745px\"/\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\nOf course, a spot on the podium and a bottle of bubbly are wonderful prizes, but the real beauty of the Malle Canyon was the fun of losing together. Planning has already begun for the 2025 edition of the Canyon; with any luck, we’ll be there this time.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://mallelondon.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eMalle London\u003c/a\u003e | Images by \u003ca href=\"https://manuelportugal.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eManuel Portugal\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\